Excellent video! 
We need to watch what the witnesses who live by the trails reported. The official timeline is absolutely correct, no mystery there. The problem is later. From the beginning: they were dropped by the taxi at the starting point of two possible trails at about 1h30pm. One trail you would climb and eventually see the entire Boquete community from the top. The other was the Pianista trail.  The girls went for the climb, but instead of going all the way up to see the city, they cut the hike short. A woman saw them coming back, and this was around 2h30pm.  The woman said later that it was impossible that the girls had gone to the top and come back in one hour or so. In other words, the girls decided to abort the first hike. That's why Frank Rosa (the owner of the shop) said the girls seemed to have hiked already. Then the girls stayed there for a while and started a new hike, this time the Pianist trail. A woman who lives by the entrance of the Pianist trail did see the girls and was concerned because it was late to start that trail. But the woman pointed out she didn't speak english and did not say a word to the girls. This was already 4h00pm or later. In other words, the timeline of the girls itinerary is perfectly coherent up to their initial emergency calls.
